        "### The Random Walk with Drift\n",
        "\n",
        "Adding a constant $\\mu$ to the random walk gives:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$y_t = \\mu + y_{t-1} + \\varepsilon_t \\tag{4.3}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "with solution $y_t = y_0 + \\mu t + \\sum_{j=1}^t \\varepsilon_j$. The series now\n",
        "has a deterministic trend — it drifts upward at rate $\\mu$ per period — but\n",
        "still contains a unit root: each $\\varepsilon_j$ shock permanently shifts the\n",
        "level. The distinction matters for forecasting:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Without drift** ($\\mu = 0$): forecasts are flat at $y_T$ with widening\n",
        "  intervals.\n",
        "- **With drift** ($\\mu \\neq 0$): forecasts grow linearly at rate $\\mu$ per\n",
        "  period, with intervals that widen around that trend."
